                          so it never competes with the main CTA above.
                          `data-cc-secondary-link` makes universe-layout's
                          stage click handler bail out without closing the
                          focused card, preserving native <a> behavior.
                          Click is `stopPropagation`'d as belt-and-braces
                          so the launch handler can never observe it. */}
                      <a
                        class="reading-entry-summary-pill"
                        href={item.href}
                        data-cc-secondary-link
                        aria-label={t('library.centerCard.bookSummaryPillAria', language)}
                      >
                        {t('library.centerCard.bookSummaryPill', language)}
                      </a>
                      <div class="cc-meta" data-cc-meta>
                        {typeof item.chapterCount === 'number' && item.chapterCount > 0 && (
                          <span class="cc-meta-item" data-cc-meta-chapters>
