         The orbit cards fan around this point on the elliptical orbit
         (top: 50% of `.library-galaxy`), so the search icon now reads
         as the luminous core that the orbit revolves around. Hidden
         automatically when a card is focused (rule below) so it never
         overlaps the centered card. Desktop is untouched — the whole
         trigger / hint / panel block is gated to ≤1023px. */
      top: 50%;
      left: 50%;
      transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      width: 52px;
      height: 52px;
      padding: 0;
      border-radius: 50%;
      border: 1px solid
        color-mix(in srgb, var(--yuval-galaxy-accent, #5eead4) 60%, transparent);
      background:
        radial-gradient(
          circle at 50% 35%,
          color-mix(in srgb, var(--yuval-galaxy-accent, #5eead4) 28%, transparent) 0%,
          color-mix(in srgb, var(--yuval-galaxy-accent, #5eead4) 8%, transparent) 55%,
          transparent 100%),
        color-mix(in srgb, var(--yuval-galaxy-bg, #00010d) 55%, transparent);
      color: var(--yuval-galaxy-accent, #5eead4);
      cursor: pointer;
      backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
